{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Each of the 2500 retraining sets was subsequently categorized by sample size (measured in the number of sentences) and relevant entity density (entities per sentence [EPS]).",
    "Sentence boundaries were determined using the sentencizer in the R tidytext (0.3.4) library [41].",
    "Sentences were used to provide a more regularized comparator as disclosure statements vary widely in length.",
    "We also focus on sentences as opposed to tokens since the number of sentences in a sample can be identified prospectively (ie, prior to annotation).",
    "Multiple regression was used to assess the linear relationship between sample size (number of sentences), entity density (EPS), and trained model F 1 -score."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Sentence boundaries were determined using the sentencizer in the R tidytext (0.3.4) library [41]."
  ]
